            <h2 id="what-must-be-done">5) What must be done: upstream prevention, not only emergency response</h2>
            <p>
              Warming centers and shelters are emergency tools. Houston should keep improving them — and scaling outreach.
              But extreme cold snaps will happen again.
              If the unsheltered count stays high, we’re agreeing (by default) to repeat the same risk cycle every winter.
            </p>

            <p>
              That’s why the focus must expand to <strong>upstream prevention</strong>: reduce the pipeline into homelessness by building durable stability earlier —
              income skills, operator habits, support structure, and real-world capability.
            </p>

